 Updated</h1><p><img src=\"http://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steam/apps/291480/extras/up_600_156.jpg?t=1504598809\"><br><br><strong>FIRST GLOBAL UPDATE OF THE YEAR: 'BLACKOUT'</strong><br><br>The global August update brings a new regional server, weapon set and rank to the game, and the crowning jewel: <strong><u><a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/linkfilter/?url=https://wf.my.com/promo/blackout/en/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  >Special Operation \u2018Blackout\u2019</a></u></strong><br><br>The \u2018Blackout\u2019 continues the story-driven Special Operation series. A sequel to \u2018Anubis\u2019 \u2013 an old-time favourite special operation, named after the Egyptian god of death himself \u2013 it brings the Warface squad together yet again. Set in Eastern Africa, the seemingly familiar desert landscape harbors new secrets: the loss of signal leads to a complete blackout in communications, taking the challenge to a whole new level. The squad can survive only by coming together and acting as a team to endure the merciless desert storm and get through the swarming cyborg hordes.<br><br>The update has also expanded the already-existent Anubis weapon series to include the most trending weapons in the game. These are now available as permanent guns. The maximum rank has been raised to 85, themed after the Winged Hussars, and formally the \u2018Lieutenant Colonel of the Heralds of Death squadron\u2019.<br><br>Owing to the growth of the North American community, a new regional server has been implemented. Situated in San Jose, it will help improve and smoothen out gameplay for the West Coast players.<br><br>Apart from that, players are now able to invite their friends via the \u2018Refer-a-friend\u2019 program, featuring rewards for both referring and referred players alike, with the ultimate referring player reward \u2013 the new Golden sidearm: AY 226.</p><br><h1>About the Game</h1><strong><u>About Warface</u></strong><br><br>Hit the front line in Warface \u